# Governance — self-editable quality gates (plan 014 S5)
#
# These files can NEUTRALIZE a coverage/quality gate by appending a `reason`
# (the ratchet trusts the allowlist) or by altering a tenant-isolation migration.
# Listing them here makes GitHub auto-request the maintainer's review on any PR
# that touches them — a visibility nudge against a silent self-weakening edit.
#
# NOTE (single-maintainer repo): branch protection's "Require review from Code
# Owners" toggle is intentionally LEFT OFF. GitHub never lets a PR author approve
# their own PR, so on a one-account repo a code-owner-review requirement can never
# be satisfied and would hard-block every PR touching these files. Mechanical
# enforcement here needs either a second maintainer or a CI gate, not this toggle.

